trans-unit.source: Return a TarFile object for the pathname name. For detailed information on TarFile objects and the keyword arguments that are allowed, see TarFile Objects.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个 TarFile 对象作为路径名。有关 TarFile 对象和允许的关键字参数的详细信息，请参见TarFile对象。

trans-unit.target: 返回一个 TarInfo 对象作为成员名称。如果在存档中找不到名称，则会引发 KeyError 。

trans-unit.source: Return a string version of object. If object is not provided, returns the empty string. Otherwise, the behavior of str() depends on whether encoding or errors is given, as follows.
trans-unit.target: 返回object的字符串版本。如果未提供object，则返回空字符串。否则， str() 的行为取决于是否给出编码或错误，如下所示。

trans-unit.source: Return a Font representation of a tk named font.
trans-unit.target: 返回tk命名的font的 Font 表示形式。

trans-unit.source: Return a CoverageResults object that contains the cumulative results of all previous calls to run, runctx and runfunc for the given Trace instance. Does not reset the accumulated trace results.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个 CoverageResults 对象，该对象包含给定 Trace 实例先前对 run ， runctx 和 runfunc 的所有先前调用的累积结果。不重置累积的跟踪结果。

trans-unit.source: Return a StackSummary object representing a list of “pre-processed” stack trace entries extracted from the traceback object tb. It is useful for alternate formatting of stack traces. The optional limit argument has the same meaning as for print_tb(). A “pre-processed” stack trace entry is a FrameSummary object containing attributes filename, lineno, name, and line representing the information that is usually printed for a stack trace. The line is a string with leading and trailing whitespace stripped; if the source is not available it is None.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个 StackSummary 对象，该对象表示从追溯对象tb中提取的“预处理”堆栈跟踪条目的列表。对于堆栈跟踪的备用格式很有用。可选的limit参数与 print_tb() 具有相同的含义。 “预处理”堆栈跟踪条目是一个 FrameSummary 对象，其中包含属性 filename ， lineno ， name 和 line ，这些属性表示通常为堆栈跟踪打印的信息。该 line 是一个字符串，前面和后面的空格都被删除了。如果来源不可用，则为 None 。

trans-unit.source: Return a Request or None in response to a redirect. This is called by the default implementations of the http_error_30*() methods when a redirection is received from the server. If a redirection should take place, return a new Request to allow http_error_30*() to perform the redirect to newurl. Otherwise, raise HTTPError if no other handler should try to handle this URL, or return None if you can’t but another handler might.
trans-unit.target: 返回 Request 或 None 响应重定向。当从服务器接收到重定向时，这由 http_error_30*() 方法的默认实现调用。如果应该进行重定向，请返回一个新 Request 以允许 http_error_30*() 执行到newurl的重定向。否则，如果没有其他处理程序应尝试处理此URL，则引发 HTTPError ;如果不能，则返回 None ，但其他处理程序可能会返回None。

trans-unit.source: Return a DOMEventStream from the given input. stream_or_string may be either a file name, or a file-like object. parser, if given, must be an XMLReader object. This function will change the document handler of the parser and activate namespace support; other parser configuration (like setting an entity resolver) must have been done in advance.
trans-unit.target: 从给定的输入返回 DOMEventStream 。stream_or_string可以是文件名，也可以是类似文件的对象。解析器（如果提供）必须是 XMLReader 对象。此函数将更改解析器的文档处理程序并激活名称空间支持；其他解析器配置（例如设置实体解析器）必须事先完成。

trans-unit.source: Return a DOMEventStream that represents the (Unicode) string.
trans-unit.target: 返回表示（Unicode）string的 DOMEventStream 。

trans-unit.target: 返回一个 ZipInfo 对象，其中包含有关存档成员名称的信息。调用 getinfo() 以获取当前未包含在存档中的名称将引发 KeyError 。

trans-unit.source: Return a concurrent.futures.Future to wait for the result from another OS thread.
trans-unit.target: 返回 concurrent.futures.Future 以等待另一个OS线程的结果。

trans-unit.source: Return a ctypes object allocated from shared memory. By default the return value is actually a synchronized wrapper for the object. The object itself can be accessed via the value attribute of a Value.
trans-unit.target: 返回从共享内存分配的 ctypes 对象。默认情况下，返回值实际上是对象的同步包装器。可以通过 Value 的value属性访问对象本身。

trans-unit.source: Return a file-like object that can be used as a temporary storage area. The file is created securely, using the same rules as mkstemp(). It will be destroyed as soon as it is closed (including an implicit close when the object is garbage collected). Under Unix, the directory entry for the file is either not created at all or is removed immediately after the file is created. Other platforms do not support this; your code should not rely on a temporary file created using this function having or not having a visible name in the file system.
trans-unit.target: 返回可以用作临时存储区的类似文件的对象。使用与 mkstemp() 相同的规则安全地创建文件。它将在关闭后立即销毁（包括在垃圾回收对象时的隐式关闭）。在Unix下，文件的目录条目根本没有创建，或者在创建文件后立即删除。其他平台不支持此功能。您的代码不应依赖使用此功能创建的临时文件，该文件在文件系统中是否具有可见名称。

trans-unit.source: Return a file object associated with the socket. The exact returned type depends on the arguments given to makefile(). These arguments are interpreted the same way as by the built-in open() function, except the only supported mode values are 'r' (default), 'w' and 'b'.
trans-unit.target: 返回与套接字关联的文件对象。返回的确切类型取决于赋予 makefile() 的参数。这些参数的解释方式与内置的 open() 函数相同，只是唯一支持的模式值为 'r' （默认）， 'w' 和 'b' 。

trans-unit.target: 返回数字的命名元组表示形式： DecimalTuple(sign, digits, exponent) 。

trans-unit.source: Return a slice object representing the set of indices specified by range(start, stop, step). The start and step arguments default to None. Slice objects have read-only data attributes start, stop and step which merely return the argument values (or their default). They have no other explicit functionality; however they are used by Numerical Python and other third party extensions. Slice objects are also generated when extended indexing syntax is used. For example: a[start:stop:step] or a[start:stop, i]. See itertools.islice() for an alternate version that returns an iterator.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个slice对象，该对象代表由 range(start, stop, step) 指定的索引集。在启动和步参数默认为 None 。切片对象具有只读数据属性 start ， stop 和 step ，这些属性仅返回参数值（或其默认值）。它们没有其他显式功能。但是，它们被数值Python和其他第三方扩展使用。使用扩展索引语法时，也会生成切片对象。例如： a[start:stop:step] 或 a[start:stop, i] 。参见 itertools.islice() 用于返回迭代器的备用版本。

trans-unit.source: Return a copy of the sequence where all ASCII tab characters are replaced by one or more ASCII spaces, depending on the current column and the given tab size. Tab positions occur every tabsize bytes (default is 8, giving tab positions at columns 0, 8, 16 and so on). To expand the sequence, the current column is set to zero and the sequence is examined byte by byte. If the byte is an ASCII tab character (b'\t'), one or more space characters are inserted in the result until the current column is equal to the next tab position. (The tab character itself is not copied.) If the current byte is an ASCII newline (b'\n') or carriage return (b'\r'), it is copied and the current column is reset to zero. Any other byte value is copied unchanged and the current column is incremented by one regardless of how the byte value is represented when printed:
trans-unit.target: 返回序列的副本，其中所有ASCII制表符都被一个或多个ASCII空格取代，具体取决于当前列和给定的制表符大小。制表符位置每一个制表符大小字节出现一次（默认为8，在列0、8、16等处给出制表符位置）。为了扩展序列，将当前列设置为零，并逐字节检查序列。如果字节是ASCII制表符（ b'\t' ），则在结果中插入一个或多个空格字符，直到当前列等于下一个制表符位置为止。 （制表符本身不会被复制。）如果当前字节是ASCII换行符（ b'\n' ）或回车符（ b'\r' ），则将其复制，并将当前列重置为零。任何其他字节值都将原样复制，并且无论打印时字节值如何表示，当前列都增加一：

trans-unit.source: Return a dictionary containing type hints for a function, method, module or class object.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个包含函数、方法、模块或类对象类型提示的字典。

trans-unit.source: Return a dictionary mapping key to value such that match(key, mapname)==value. Note that both keys and values of the dictionary are arbitrary arrays of bytes.
trans-unit.target: 返回字典映射键到value，这样 match(key, mapname)==value 。请注意，字典的键和值都是字节的任意数组。

trans-unit.source: Return a dictionary mapping each thread’s identifier to the topmost stack frame currently active in that thread at the time the function is called. Note that functions in the traceback module can build the call stack given such a frame.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个字典，该字典将每个线程的标识符映射到调用该函数时该线程中当前活动的最顶层堆栈帧。注意，给定这样的框架， traceback 模块中的函数可以构建调用堆栈。

trans-unit.source: Return a dictionary mapping module-level class names to class descriptors. If possible, descriptors for imported base classes are included. Parameter module is a string with the name of the module to read; it may be the name of a module within a package. If given, path is a sequence of directory paths prepended to sys.path, which is used to locate the module source code.
trans-unit.target: 返回将模块级类名称映射到类描述符的字典。如果可能，将包括导入的基类的描述符。参数module是一个字符串，其中包含要读取的模块的名称；它可能是包中模块的名称。如果给定，则path是 sys.path 之前的目录路径序列，用于定位模块源代码。

trans-unit.source: Return a dictionary of sequence names mapped to key lists. If there are no sequences, the empty dictionary is returned.
trans-unit.target: 返回映射到键列表的序列名的字典,如果没有序列,则返回空字典。如果没有序列,则返回空字典。

trans-unit.source: Return a dictionary representing the current global symbol table. This is always the dictionary of the current module (inside a function or method, this is the module where it is defined, not the module from which it is called).
trans-unit.target: 返回一个代表当前全局符号表的字典。这总是当前模块的字典(在函数或方法中,这是定义它的模块,而不是调用它的模块)。

trans-unit.source: Return a dictionary-based tree containing a function or class descriptors for each function and class defined in the module with a def or class statement. The returned dictionary maps module-level function and class names to their descriptors. Nested objects are entered into the children dictionary of their parent. As with readmodule, module names the module to be read and path is prepended to sys.path. If the module being read is a package, the returned dictionary has a key '__path__' whose value is a list containing the package search path.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个基于字典的树，其中包含使用 def 或 class 语句在模块中定义的每个函数和类的函数或类描述符。返回的字典将模块级函数和类名映射到其描述符。嵌套对象被输入到其父级的子级字典中。与readmodule一样，模块名称为要读取的模块，路径位于sys.path之前。如果正在读取的模块是包，则返回的字典具有键 '__path__' 其值是包含包搜索路径的列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a duplicate of file descriptor fd. The new file descriptor is non-inheritable.
trans-unit.target: 返回文件描述符fd的副本。新的文件描述符是不可继承的。

trans-unit.source: Return a duplicate of the context.
trans-unit.target: 返回上下文的副本。

trans-unit.source: Return a factor F such that rms(add(fragment, mul(reference, -F))) is minimal, i.e., return the factor with which you should multiply reference to make it match as well as possible to fragment. The fragments should both contain 2-byte samples.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个因子F，以使 rms(add(fragment, mul(reference, -F))) 最小，即，返回您应乘以引用以使其匹配并尽可能使其片段化的因子。片段都应包含2字节样本。

trans-unit.source: Return a file descriptor referring to the process pid. This descriptor can be used to perform process management without races and signals. The flags argument is provided for future extensions; no flag values are currently defined.
trans-unit.target: 返回引用进程pid的文件描述符。该描述符可用于执行过程管理，而不会出现种族和信号。该标志参数设置为将来的扩展; 当前未定义标志值。

trans-unit.source: Return a file-like object, open to file, but read from or written to by the pipeline. Note that only one of 'r', 'w' may be given.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个类似文件的对象，该对象可打开file，但可以从管道中读取或写入。注意，只能给出 'r' 和 'w' 中的一个。

trans-unit.source: Return a file-like representation of the message corresponding to key, or raise a KeyError exception if no such message exists. The file-like object behaves as if open in binary mode. This file should be closed once it is no longer needed.
trans-unit.target: 返回与key对应的消息的类似文件的表示形式，如果不存在此类消息，则引发 KeyError 异常。类似于文件的对象的行为就像在二进制模式下打开一样。一旦不再需要该文件，则应将其关闭。

trans-unit.source: Return a float with the magnitude (absolute value) of x but the sign of y. On platforms that support signed zeros, copysign(1.0, -0.0) returns -1.0.
trans-unit.target: 返回浮点数，其浮点数为x，但符号为y。在支持带符号零的平台上， copysign(1.0, -0.0) 返回-1.0。

trans-unit.source: Return a floating point number constructed from a number or string x.
trans-unit.target: 返回由数字或字符串x构造的浮点数。

trans-unit.source: Return a formatted dump of the tree in node. This is mainly useful for debugging purposes. If annotate_fields is true (by default), the returned string will show the names and the values for fields. If annotate_fields is false, the result string will be more compact by omitting unambiguous field names. Attributes such as line numbers and column offsets are not dumped by default. If this is wanted, include_attributes can be set to true.
trans-unit.target: 返回node中树的格式化转储。这主要用于调试目的。如果annotate_fields为true（默认情况下），则返回的字符串将显示字段的名称和值。如果annotate_fields为false，则省略明确的字段名称，结果字符串将更加紧凑。默认情况下，不转储诸如行号和列偏移量的属性。如果需要，可以将include_attributes设置为true。

trans-unit.source: Return a formatted multi-line string with detailed code object information for the supplied function, generator, asynchronous generator, coroutine, method, source code string or code object.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个格式化的多行字符串,包含所提供的函数、生成器、异步生成器、coroutine、方法、源代码字符串或代码对象的详细代码对象信息。

trans-unit.source: Return a formatted multi-line string with detailed information about the code object, like code_info().
trans-unit.target: 返回格式化的多行字符串，其中包含有关代码对象的详细信息，例如 code_info() 。

trans-unit.source: Return a formatted view of the bytecode operations (the same as printed by dis.dis(), but returned as a multi-line string).
trans-unit.target: 返回字节码操作的格式化视图（与 dis.dis() 打印的相同，但以多行字符串形式返回）。

trans-unit.source: Return a fragment that has all samples in the original fragment multiplied by the floating-point value factor. Samples are truncated in case of overflow.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个片段，该片段具有原始片段中的所有样本乘以浮点值factor。如果发生溢出，样本将被截断。

trans-unit.source: Return a fragment that is the original fragment with a bias added to each sample. Samples wrap around in case of overflow.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个片段,是原始片段,每个样本都加了一个偏置。样本环绕,以防溢出。

trans-unit.source: Return a fragment which is the addition of the two samples passed as parameters. width is the sample width in bytes, either 1, 2, 3 or 4. Both fragments should have the same length. Samples are truncated in case of overflow.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个片段，该片段是作为参数传递的两个样本的和。宽度以字节为单位的样品宽度，或是 1 ， 2 ， 3 或 4 。两个片段应具有相同的长度。如果发生溢出，样本将被截断。

trans-unit.source: Return a frame object from the call stack. If optional integer depth is given, return the frame object that many calls below the top of the stack. If that is deeper than the call stack, ValueError is raised. The default for depth is zero, returning the frame at the top of the call stack.
trans-unit.target: 从调用堆栈返回一个框架对象。如果给出了可选的整数深度，则返回在堆栈顶部下方被许多调用的框架对象。如果那比调用堆栈深，则引发 ValueError 。深度的默认值为零，将帧返回到调用堆栈的顶部。

trans-unit.source: Return a fully qualified domain name for name. If name is omitted or empty, it is interpreted as the local host. To find the fully qualified name, the hostname returned by gethostbyaddr() is checked, followed by aliases for the host, if available. The first name which includes a period is selected. In case no fully qualified domain name is available, the hostname as returned by gethostname() is returned.
trans-unit.target: 返回的一个完全合格的域名名称。如果name省略或为空，则将其解释为本地主机。要查找标准名称，将检查由 gethostbyaddr() 返回的主机名，然后是主机的别名（如果有）。选择包含句点的名字。如果没有完全限定的域名可用，则返回由 gethostname() 返回的主机名。

trans-unit.source: Return a guess for whether wsgi.url_scheme should be “http” or “https”, by checking for a HTTPS environment variable in the environ dictionary. The return value is a string.
trans-unit.target: 通过检查环境字典中的 HTTPS 环境变量，返回 wsgi.url_scheme 应该是“ http”还是“ https” 的猜测。返回值是一个字符串。

trans-unit.source: Return a header containing abbreviated weekday names. n specifies the width in characters for one weekday.
trans-unit.target: 返回包含缩写的工作日名称的标头。n指定一个工作日的宽度（以字符为单位）。

trans-unit.source: Return a human-readable message describing the error condition.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个描述错误条件的可读信息。

trans-unit.source: Return a key suitable for sorting between networks and addresses. Address and Network objects are not sortable by default; they’re fundamentally different, so the expression:
trans-unit.target: 返回适合在网络和地址之间排序的密钥。默认情况下，地址和网络对象不可排序；它们根本不同，因此表达式：

trans-unit.source: Return a list containing a ZipInfo object for each member of the archive. The objects are in the same order as their entries in the actual ZIP file on disk if an existing archive was opened.
trans-unit.target: 返回包含每个存档成员的 ZipInfo 对象的列表。如果打开了现有存档，则对象的顺序与它们在磁盘上实际ZIP文件中的条目的顺序相同。

trans-unit.source: Return a list containing all global site-packages directories.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个包含所有全局站点包目录的列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list containing the character set names in the message. If the message is a multipart, then the list will contain one element for each subpart in the payload, otherwise, it will be a list of length 1.
trans-unit.target: 返回包含消息中字符集名称的列表。如果消息是multipart，则列表将为有效负载中的每个子部分包含一个元素，否则，它将是长度为1的列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list containing the names of the entries in the directory given by path. The list is in arbitrary order, and does not include the special entries '.' and '..' even if they are present in the directory.
trans-unit.target: 返回包含path指定的目录中条目名称的列表。该列表以任意顺序排列，并且不包括特殊条目 '.' 和 '..' 即使它们存在于目录中。

trans-unit.source: Return a list containing the names of the entries in the directory given by path. The list is in arbitrary order, and does not include the special entries '.' and '..' even if they are present in the directory. If a file is removed from or added to the directory during the call of this function, whether a name for that file be included is unspecified.
trans-unit.target: 返回包含path指定的目录中条目名称的列表。该列表以任意顺序排列，并且不包括特殊条目 '.' 和 '..' 即使它们存在于目录中）。如果在调用此函数期间从目录中删除文件或将文件添加到目录中，则不确定是否包含该文件的名称。

trans-unit.source: Return a list containing the tty attributes for file descriptor fd, as follows: [iflag, oflag, cflag, lflag, ispeed, ospeed, cc] where cc is a list of the tty special characters (each a string of length 1, except the items with indices VMIN and VTIME, which are integers when these fields are defined). The interpretation of the flags and the speeds as well as the indexing in the cc array must be done using the symbolic constants defined in the termios module.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个包含文件描述符fd的tty属性的列表，如下所示： [iflag, oflag, cflag, lflag, ispeed, ospeed, cc] ，其中cc是tty特殊字符的列表（每个字符串的长度为1，除了索引为 VMIN 和 VTIME 的项，在定义这些字段时为整数）。标志和速度的解释以及cc数组中的索引必须使用 termios 模块中定义的符号常量来完成。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of (header, value) tuples.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个(header,value)元组的列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of 2-tuples containing all the message’s field headers and values.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个包含所有消息字段标题和值的2元组列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of 2-tuples containing all variables and their values in the context object.
trans-unit.target: 返回包含上下文对象中所有变量及其值的2-tuples列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of Symbol instances for names in the table.
trans-unit.target: 返回用于表中名称的 Symbol 实例列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of all Thread objects currently alive. The list includes daemonic threads, dummy thread objects created by current_thread(), and the main thread. It excludes terminated threads and threads that have not yet been started.
trans-unit.target: 返回当前活动的所有 Thread 对象的列表。该列表包括守护线程，由 current_thread() 创建的虚拟线程对象和主线程。它不包括终止的线程和尚未启动的线程。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of all available group entries, in arbitrary order.
trans-unit.target: 返回所有可用的组条目列表,按任意顺序排列。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of all available password database entries, in arbitrary order.
trans-unit.target: 按任意顺序返回所有可用的密码数据库条目列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of all available shadow password database entries, in arbitrary order.
trans-unit.target: 按任意顺序返回所有可用的影子密码数据库条目列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of all registered formats for unpacking. Each element of the returned sequence is a tuple (name, extensions, description).
trans-unit.target: 返回所有已注册格式的列表以进行打包。返回序列的每个元素都是一个元组 (name, extensions, description) 。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of all the keys used in the dictionary d.
trans-unit.target: 返回字典d中使用的所有键的列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of all the message’s field values.
trans-unit.target: 返回所有消息字段值的列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of all the message’s header field names.
trans-unit.target: 返回所有消息标题字段名称的列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of all the values for the field named name. If there are no such named headers in the message, failobj is returned (defaults to None).
trans-unit.target: 返回名为name的字段的所有值的列表。如果消息中没有这样的命名头，则返回failobj（默认为 None ）。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of all the values for the named header.
trans-unit.target: 返回指定头的所有值的列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of all valid maps.
trans-unit.target: 返回所有有效地图的列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of all variables in the context object.
trans-unit.target: 返回上下文对象中所有变量的列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of all variables’ values in the context object.
trans-unit.target: 返回上下文对象中所有变量值的列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of all weak reference and proxy objects which refer to object.
trans-unit.target: 回到这指的是所有弱引用和代理对象的列表对象。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of archive members by name.
trans-unit.target: 按名称返回档案成员列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of command line arguments reproducing the current optimization settings in sys.flags.
trans-unit.target: 返回命令行参数列表，该列表重现 sys.flags 中的当前优化设置。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of command line arguments reproducing the current settings in sys.flags and sys.warnoptions.
trans-unit.target: 返回命令行参数列表，这些参数在 sys.flags 和 sys.warnoptions 中再现当前设置。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of file names as returned by the NLST command. The optional argument is a directory to list (default is the current server directory). Multiple arguments can be used to pass non-standard options to the NLST command.
trans-unit.target: 返回 NLST 命令返回的文件名列表。可选参数是要列出的目录（默认为当前服务器目录）。可以使用多个参数将非标准选项传递给 NLST 命令。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of frame records for the caller’s stack. The first entry in the returned list represents the caller; the last entry represents the outermost call on the stack.
trans-unit.target: 返回调用者堆栈的帧记录列表。返回列表中的第一项代表呼叫者；最后一个条目表示堆栈上的最外层调用。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of frame records for the stack between the current frame and the frame in which an exception currently being handled was raised in. The first entry in the list represents the caller; the last entry represents where the exception was raised.
trans-unit.target: 返回当前帧和当前正在处理的异常发生的帧之间堆栈的帧记录列表。列表中第一个条目代表调用者;最后一个条目代表异常发生的位置。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of labels on the message.
trans-unit.target: 返回信息上的标签列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of markers in the audio file. A marker consists of a tuple of three elements. The first is the mark ID (an integer), the second is the mark position in frames from the beginning of the data (an integer), the third is the name of the mark (a string).
trans-unit.target: 返回音频文件中的标记列表。一个标记由三个元素组成。第一个是标记ID(一个整数),第二个是标记在数据开始的帧中的位置(一个整数),第三个是标记的名称(一个字符串)。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of names of all currently available turtle shapes.
trans-unit.target: 返回当前所有可用的海龟形状的名称列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of names of symbols in this table.
trans-unit.target: 返回本表中的符号名称列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of namespaces bound to this name.
trans-unit.target: 返回与此名称绑定的命名空间列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of network interface information (index int, name string) tuples. OSError if the system call fails.
trans-unit.target: 返回网络接口信息（索引int，名称字符串）元组的列表。如果系统调用失败，则为 OSError 。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of objects directly referred to by any of the arguments. The referents returned are those objects visited by the arguments’ C-level tp_traverse methods (if any), and may not be all objects actually directly reachable. tp_traverse methods are supported only by objects that support garbage collection, and are only required to visit objects that may be involved in a cycle. So, for example, if an integer is directly reachable from an argument, that integer object may or may not appear in the result list.
trans-unit.target: 返回由任何参数直接引用的对象的列表。返回的对象是参数的C级 tp_traverse 方法（如果有）访问的那些对象，并且可能不是实际上直接可访问的所有对象。 tp_traverse 方法仅受支持垃圾收集的对象支持，并且仅需要访问可能涉及循环的对象。因此，例如，如果从参数直接可访问整数，则该整数对象可能会或可能不会出现在结果列表中。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of objects directly referred to by any of the arguments. The referents returned are those objects visited by the arguments’ C-level tp_traverse methods (if any), and may not be all objects actually directly reachable. tp_traverse methods are supported only by objects that support garbage collection, and are only required to visit objects that may be involved in a cycle. So, for example, if an integer is directly reachable from an argument, that integer object may or may not appear in the result list.
trans-unit.target: 返回由任何参数直接引用的对象的列表。返回的对象是参数的C级 tp_traverse 方法（如果有）访问的那些对象，并且可能不是实际上直接可访问的所有对象。 tp_traverse 方法仅受支持垃圾回收的对象支持，并且仅需要访问可能涉及循环的对象。因此，例如，如果从参数直接可访问整数，则该整数对象可能会或可能不会出现在结果列表中。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of options available in the specified section.
trans-unit.target: 返回指定部分中可用的选项列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of source lines and starting line number for an object. The argument may be a module, class, method, function, traceback, frame, or code object. The source code is returned as a list of the lines corresponding to the object and the line number indicates where in the original source file the first line of code was found. An OSError is raised if the source code cannot be retrieved.
trans-unit.target: 返回对象的源代码行和起始行号的列表。参数可以是模块，类，方法，函数，回溯，框架或代码对象。返回源代码作为与对象相对应的行的列表，并且行号指示在原始源文件中找到第一行代码的位置。一个 OSError 如果源代码不能被检索上升。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of supported formats for archiving. Each element of the returned sequence is a tuple (name, description).
trans-unit.target: 返回用于归档的受支持格式的列表。返回序列的每个元素都是一个元组 (name, description) 。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of the DocTests that are defined by obj’s docstring, or by any of its contained objects’ docstrings.
trans-unit.target: 返回由obj的文档字符串或其任何包含的对象的文档字符串定义的 DocTest 的列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of the n most common elements and their counts from the most common to the least. If n is omitted or None, most_common() returns all elements in the counter. Elements with equal counts are ordered in the order first encountered:
trans-unit.target: 返回n个最常见元素的列表及其从最常见到最小的计数。如果省略n或 None ，则 most_common() 返回计数器中的所有元素。具有相等计数的元素按首先遇到的顺序排序：

trans-unit.source: Return a list of the best “good enough” matches. word is a sequence for which close matches are desired (typically a string), and possibilities is a list of sequences against which to match word (typically a list of strings).
trans-unit.target: 返回最佳的“足够好”的匹配项列表。word是需要紧密匹配的序列（通常是字符串），而可能性是要匹配单词的序列列表（通常是字符串列表）。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of the extended filesystem attributes on path. The attributes in the list are represented as strings decoded with the filesystem encoding. If path is None, listxattr() will examine the current directory.
trans-unit.target: 返回path上扩展文件系统属性的列表。列表中的属性表示为使用文件系统编码解码的字符串。如果path为 None ，则 listxattr() 将检查当前目录。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of the lines in the binary sequence, breaking at ASCII line boundaries. This method uses the universal newlines approach to splitting lines. Line breaks are not included in the resulting list unless keepends is given and true.
trans-unit.target: 返回二进制序列中的行列表，在ASCII行边界处中断。此方法使用通用换行符方法来分割行。除非给出了keepends且为true，否则换行符不包含在结果列表中。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of the lines in the binary sequence, breaking at ASCII line boundaries. This method uses the universal newlines approach to splitting lines. Line breaks are not included in the resulting list unless keepends is given and true.
trans-unit.target: 返回二进制序列中的行列表，在ASCII行边界处中断。此方法使用通用换行符方法来分割行。除非给出了keepends且为true，否则换行符不包含在结果列表中。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of the lines in the string, breaking at line boundaries. Line breaks are not included in the resulting list unless keepends is given and true.
trans-unit.target: 返回字符串中的行列表，在行边界处中断。除非给出了keepends且为true，否则换行符不包含在结果列表中。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of the most frequently occurring values in the order they were first encountered in the data. Will return more than one result if there are multiple modes or an empty list if the data is empty:
trans-unit.target: 以最先出现的值的顺序返回它们的列表，该值最先在数据中遇到。如果有多种模式，将返回多个结果；如果数据为空，将返回一个空列表：

trans-unit.source: Return a list of the names of all folders.
trans-unit.target: 返回所有文件夹的名称列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of the names of all user-defined labels used in the mailbox.
trans-unit.target: 返回邮箱中使用的所有用户自定义标签的名称列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of the names of sequences that include this message.
trans-unit.target: 返回包含此消息的序列名称的列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of the nested symbol tables.
trans-unit.target: 返回嵌套符号表的列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of the sections available; the default section is not included in the list.
trans-unit.target: 返回可用部分的列表；在默认的部分不包括在列表中。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of the weeks in the month month of the year as full weeks. Weeks are lists of seven datetime.date objects.
trans-unit.target: 将一年中月份月份中的周列表返回为完整周。周是七个 datetime.date 对象的列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of the weeks in the month month of the year as full weeks. Weeks are lists of seven day numbers.
trans-unit.target: 将一年中月份月份中的周列表返回为完整周。周是7天数字的列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of the weeks in the month month of the year as full weeks. Weeks are lists of seven tuples of day numbers and weekday numbers.
trans-unit.target: 将一年中月份月份中的周列表返回为完整周。星期是由日期和工作日数字组成的七个元组的列表。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of the words in the string, using sep as the delimiter string. If maxsplit is given, at most maxsplit splits are done (thus, the list will have at most maxsplit+1 elements). If maxsplit is not specified or -1, then there is no limit on the number of splits (all possible splits are made).
trans-unit.target: 使用sep作为分隔符字符串，返回字符串中单词的列表。如果指定了maxsplit，则最多完成maxsplit个分割（因此，列表最多包含 maxsplit+1 个元素）。如果未指定maxsplit或 -1 ，则分割数没有限制（已进行所有可能的分割）。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of the words in the string, using sep as the delimiter string. If maxsplit is given, at most maxsplit splits are done, the rightmost ones. If sep is not specified or None, any whitespace string is a separator. Except for splitting from the right, rsplit() behaves like split() which is described in detail below.
trans-unit.target: 使用sep作为分隔符字符串，返回字符串中单词的列表。如果给出了maxsplit，则最多完成maxsplit拆分，最右边的拆分完成。如果未指定sep或 None ，则任何空格字符串都是分隔符。除了从右侧拆分外， rsplit() 的行为类似于 split() ，下面将对其进行详细说明。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of three per-generation dictionaries containing collection statistics since interpreter start. The number of keys may change in the future, but currently each dictionary will contain the following items:
trans-unit.target: 返回一个包含自解释器启动以来的三个每代字典的列表,其中包含集合统计。键的数量将来可能会改变,但目前每个字典将包含以下项目。

trans-unit.source: Return a list of tuples (header_name, header_value) of the Request headers.
trans-unit.target: 返回请求头的元组列表(header_name,header_value)。

trans-unit.source: Return a list with the n largest elements from the dataset defined by iterable. key, if provided, specifies a function of one argument that is used to extract a comparison key from each element in iterable (for example, key=str.lower). Equivalent to: sorted(iterable, key=key, reverse=True)[:n].
trans-unit.target: 从iterable定义的数据集中返回具有n个最大元素的列表。key（如果提供）指定一个参数的功能，该参数用于从iterable中的每个元素中提取比较键（例如， key=str.lower ）。等效于： sorted(iterable, key=key, reverse=True)[:n] 。

trans-unit.source: Return a list with the n smallest elements from the dataset defined by iterable. key, if provided, specifies a function of one argument that is used to extract a comparison key from each element in iterable (for example, key=str.lower). Equivalent to: sorted(iterable, key=key)[:n].
trans-unit.target: 从iterable定义的数据集中返回包含n个最小元素的列表。key（如果提供）指定一个参数的功能，该参数用于从iterable中的每个元素中提取比较键（例如， key=str.lower ）。等效于： sorted(iterable, key=key)[:n] 。

trans-unit.source: Return a logger with the specified name or, if name is None, return a logger which is the root logger of the hierarchy. If specified, the name is typically a dot-separated hierarchical name like ‘a’, ‘a.b’ or ‘a.b.c.d’. Choice of these names is entirely up to the developer who is using logging.
trans-unit.target: 返回具有指定名称的记录器，或者，如果名称为 None ，则返回作为层次结构的根记录器的记录器。如果指定，则名称通常是点分隔的层次结构名称，例如'a'，'a.b'或'abcd'。这些名称的选择完全取决于正在使用日志记录的开发人员。

trans-unit.source: Return a logical OR of all video attributes supported by the terminal. This information is useful when a curses program needs complete control over the appearance of the screen.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个终端支持的所有视频属性的逻辑OR。当一个诅咒程序需要完全控制屏幕的外观时,这个信息很有用。

trans-unit.source: Return a mapping of file objects to selector keys.
trans-unit.target: 返回文件对象与选择键的映射。

trans-unit.source: Return a measure of the sequences’ similarity as a float in the range [0, 1].
trans-unit.target: 以[0，1]范围内的浮点数形式返回序列相似性的度量。

trans-unit.source: Return a message object structure from a bytes-like object. This is equivalent to BytesParser().parsebytes(s). Optional _class and policy are interpreted as with the BytesParser class constructor.
trans-unit.target: 从类似字节的对象返回消息对象结构。这等效于 BytesParser().parsebytes(s) 。可选的_class和policy与 BytesParser 类构造函数一样解释。

trans-unit.source: Return a message object structure from a bytes-like object. This is equivalent to BytesParser().parsebytes(s). Optional _class and policy are interpreted as with the BytesParser class constructor.
trans-unit.target: 从类似字节的对象返回消息对象结构。这等效于 BytesParser().parsebytes(s) 。可选的_class和policy与 BytesParser 类构造函数一样解释。

trans-unit.source: Return a message object structure from a string. This is equivalent to Parser().parsestr(s). _class and policy are interpreted as with the Parser class constructor.
trans-unit.target: 从字符串返回消息对象结构。这等效于 Parser().parsestr(s) 。_class和policy的解释与 Parser 类的构造函数相同。

trans-unit.source: Return a message object structure tree from an open file object. This is equivalent to Parser().parse(fp). _class and policy are interpreted as with the Parser class constructor.
trans-unit.target: 从打开的文件对象返回消息对象结构树。这等效于 Parser().parse(fp) 。_class和policy的解释与 Parser 类的构造函数相同。

trans-unit.source: Return a message object structure tree from an open file object. This is equivalent to Parser().parse(fp). _class and policy are interpreted as with the Parser class constructor.
trans-unit.target: 从打开的文件对象返回消息对象结构树。这等效于 Parser().parse(fp) 。_class和policy的解析方式与 Parser 类的构造方法相同。

trans-unit.source: Return a message object structure tree from an open binary file object. This is equivalent to BytesParser().parse(fp). _class and policy are interpreted as with the BytesParser class constructor.
trans-unit.target: 从打开的二进制文件对象返回消息对象结构树。这等效于 BytesParser().parse(fp) 。_class和policy的解释与 BytesParser 类的构造函数相同。

trans-unit.source: Return a message object structure tree from an open binary file object. This is equivalent to BytesParser().parse(fp). _class and policy are interpreted as with the BytesParser class constructor.
trans-unit.target: 从打开的二进制文件对象返回消息对象结构树。这等效于 BytesParser().parse(fp) 。_class和policy的解释与 BytesParser 类的构造函数相同。

trans-unit.source: Return a month’s calendar as an HTML table. If withyear is true the year will be included in the header, otherwise just the month name will be used.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个月的日历作为HTML表。如果withyear为true，则年份将包含在标题中，否则仅使用月份名称。

trans-unit.source: Return a month’s calendar in a multi-line string. If w is provided, it specifies the width of the date columns, which are centered. If l is given, it specifies the number of lines that each week will use. Depends on the first weekday as specified in the constructor or set by the setfirstweekday() method.
trans-unit.target: 以多行字符串返回一个月的日历。如果提供w，它将指定居中的日期列的宽度。如果给出l，则它指定每周将使用的行数。取决于构造函数中指定的或由 setfirstweekday() 方法设置的第一个工作日。

trans-unit.source: Return a named tuple describing the Windows version currently running. The named elements are major, minor, build, platform, service_pack, service_pack_minor, service_pack_major, suite_mask, product_type and platform_version. service_pack contains a string, platform_version a 3-tuple and all other values are integers. The components can also be accessed by name, so sys.getwindowsversion()[0] is equivalent to sys.getwindowsversion().major. For compatibility with prior versions, only the first 5 elements are retrievable by indexing.
trans-unit.target: 返回描述当前运行的Windows版本的命名元组。命名的元素是major，minor，build，platform，service_pack，service_pack_minor，service_pack_major，suite_mask，product_type和platform_version。service_pack包含一个字符串，platform_version包含一个三元组，所有其他值都是整数。也可以通过名称访问组件，因此 sys.getwindowsversion()[0] 等效于 sys.getwindowsversion().major 。为了与以前的版本兼容，只能通过索引检索前5个元素。

trans-unit.source: Return a network interface index number corresponding to an interface name. OSError if no interface with the given name exists.
trans-unit.target: 返回与接口名称相对应的网络接口索引号。如果没有给定名称的接口，则发生 OSError 。

trans-unit.source: Return a network interface name corresponding to an interface index number. OSError if no interface with the given index exists.
trans-unit.target: 返回与接口索引号相对应的网络接口名称。如果不存在具有给定索引的接口，则发生 OSError 。

trans-unit.source: Return a new “bytes” object, which is an immutable sequence of integers in the range 0 <= x < 256. bytes is an immutable version of bytearray – it has the same non-mutating methods and the same indexing and slicing behavior.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个新的“ bytes”对象，该对象是不可变的整数序列，范围为 0 <= x < 256 。 bytes 是字节 bytearray 的不变版本–它具有相同的非变异方法以及相同的索引和切片行为。

trans-unit.source: Return a new window, whose left-upper corner is at (begin_y, begin_x), and whose height/width is nlines/ncols.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个新窗口，其左上角为 (begin_y, begin_x) ，其高度/宽度为nlines / ncols。

trans-unit.source: Return a new datetime object whose date components are equal to the given date object’s, and whose time components are equal to the given time object’s. If the tzinfo argument is provided, its value is used to set the tzinfo attribute of the result, otherwise the tzinfo attribute of the time argument is used.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个新的 datetime 对象，其日期分量等于给定 date 对象的日期分量，并且其时间分量等于给定 time 对象的日期分量。如果tzinfo被提供的参数，其值被用于设置 tzinfo 结果的属性，否则 tzinfo 所述的属性的时间的参数被使用。

trans-unit.source: Return a new Policy instance whose attributes have the same values as the current instance, except where those attributes are given new values by the keyword arguments.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个新的 Policy 实例，该实例的属性与当前实例具有相同的值，除非这些属性由关键字参数赋予新的值。

trans-unit.source: Return a new partialmethod descriptor which behaves like partial except that it is designed to be used as a method definition rather than being directly callable.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个新的 partialmethod 描述符，该描述符的行为类似于 partial ,只是它被设计为用作方法定义而不是可直接调用的。

trans-unit.source: Return a new Control object. An entry in the Control table is made with the specified parameters.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个新的 Control 对象。使用指定的参数在“ Control 表中创建一个条目。

trans-unit.source: Return a new Dialog object. An entry in the Dialog table is made, with the specified coordinates, dialog attributes, title, name of the first, default, and cancel controls.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个新的 Dialog 对象。在 Dialog 表中创建一个条目，其中包含指定的坐标，对话框属性，标题，第一个控件的名称，默认控件和取消控件。

trans-unit.source: Return a new NNTP object, representing a connection to the NNTP server running on host host, listening at port port. An optional timeout can be specified for the socket connection. If the optional user and password are provided, or if suitable credentials are present in /.netrc and the optional flag usenetrc is true, the AUTHINFO USER and AUTHINFO PASS commands are used to identify and authenticate the user to the server. If the optional flag readermode is true, then a mode reader command is sent before authentication is performed. Reader mode is sometimes necessary if you are connecting to an NNTP server on the local machine and intend to call reader-specific commands, such as group. If you get unexpected NNTPPermanentErrors, you might need to set readermode. The NNTP class supports the with statement to unconditionally consume OSError exceptions and to close the NNTP connection when done, e.g.:
trans-unit.target: 返回一个新的 NNTP 对象，表示与主机host上运行的NNTP服务器的连接，侦听端口port。可以为套接字连接指定一个可选的超时时间。如果提供了可选的用户名和密码，或者 /.netrc 中存在适当的凭据，并且可选标志usenetrc为true，则 AUTHINFO USER 和 AUTHINFO PASS 命令用于向服务器标识用户并对其进行身份验证。如果可选标志readermode为true，则为 mode reader 在验证之前发送命令。如果要连接到本地计算机上的NNTP服务器并打算调用特定于读取器的命令（例如 group )，则有时需要读取器模式。如果收到意外的 NNTPPermanentError ，则可能需要设置readermode。该 NNTP 类支持 with 语句无条件消耗 OSError 例外，完成后关闭NNTP连接，例如：

trans-unit.source: Return a new NNTP_SSL object, representing an encrypted connection to the NNTP server running on host host, listening at port port. NNTP_SSL objects have the same methods as NNTP objects. If port is omitted, port 563 (NNTPS) is used. ssl_context is also optional, and is a SSLContext object. Please read Security considerations for best practices. All other parameters behave the same as for NNTP.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个新的 NNTP_SSL 对象，表示与主机host上运行的NNTP服务器的加密连接，侦听端口port。 NNTP_SSL 对象具有与 NNTP 对象相同的方法。如果端口被省略，端口563（NNTPS）被使用。ssl_context也是可选的，并且是 SSLContext 对象。请阅读安全性注意事项以获取最佳实践。所有其他参数的行为与 NNTP 相同。

trans-unit.source: Return a new SSLContext object with default settings for the given purpose. The settings are chosen by the ssl module, and usually represent a higher security level than when calling the SSLContext constructor directly.
trans-unit.target: 为给定目的返回一个具有默认设置的新 SSLContext 对象。这些设置由 ssl 模块选择，并且与直接调用 SSLContext 构造函数相比，它们通常表示更高的安全级别。

trans-unit.source: Return a new dict which maps field names to their corresponding values:
trans-unit.target: 返回一个新的 dict ，将字段名称映射到其对应的值：

trans-unit.source: Return a new frozenset object, optionally with elements taken from iterable. frozenset is a built-in class. See frozenset and Set Types — set, frozenset for documentation about this class.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个新的 frozenset 对象，可以选择从iterable获取元素。 frozenset 是一个内置类。有关 frozenset 的文档，请参见Frozenset和Set Types-set，frozenset。

trans-unit.source: Return a new set object, optionally with elements taken from iterable. set is a built-in class. See set and Set Types — set, frozenset for documentation about this class.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个新的 set 对象，可以选择从iterable获取元素。 set 是一个内置类。有关此类的文档，请参见 set 和Set Types-set，frozenset。

trans-unit.source: Return a new Document object (the root of the DOM), with a child Element object having the given namespaceUri and qualifiedName. The doctype must be a DocumentType object created by createDocumentType(), or None. In the Python DOM API, the first two arguments can also be None in order to indicate that no Element child is to be created.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个新的 Document 对象（DOM的根），其子 Element 对象具有给定的namespaceUri和qualifiedName。的文档类型必须是 DocumentType 通过创建的对象 createDocumentType() 或 None 。在Python DOM API中，前两个参数也可以是 None ，以指示将不创建任何 Element 子级。

trans-unit.source: Return a new DocumentType object that encapsulates the given qualifiedName, publicId, and systemId strings, representing the information contained in an XML document type declaration.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个新的 DocumentType 对象，该对象封装了给定的qualifiedName，publicId和systemId字符串，这些字符串表示XML文档类型声明中包含的信息。

trans-unit.source: Return a new Struct object which writes and reads binary data according to the format string format. Creating a Struct object once and calling its methods is more efficient than calling the struct functions with the same format since the format string only needs to be compiled once.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个新的Struct对象，该对象根据格式字符串format写入和读取二进制数据。一次创建一个Struct对象并调用其方法比使用相同格式的 struct 函数更有效，因为格式字符串只需要编译一次。

trans-unit.source: Return a new UUID, in the format that MSI typically requires (i.e. in curly braces, and with all hexdigits in upper-case).
trans-unit.target: 返回一个新的UUID,格式为MSI通常要求的格式(即用大括号,并且所有的十六进制数字都是大写的)。

trans-unit.source: Return a new array of bytes. The bytearray class is a mutable sequence of integers in the range 0 <= x < 256. It has most of the usual methods of mutable sequences, described in Mutable Sequence Types, as well as most methods that the bytes type has, see Bytes and Bytearray Operations.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个新的字节数组。该 bytearray 类是整数的范围内的可变序列0 <= X <256，具有最的可变序列，在所描述的常规方法的可变序列类型，以及大多数方法，该 bytes 类型已见字节和字节数组操作。

trans-unit.source: Return a new database object by calling MsiOpenDatabase. path is the file name of the MSI file; persist can be one of the constants MSIDBOPEN_CREATEDIRECT, MSIDBOPEN_CREATE, MSIDBOPEN_DIRECT, MSIDBOPEN_READONLY, or MSIDBOPEN_TRANSACT, and may include the flag MSIDBOPEN_PATCHFILE. See the Microsoft documentation for the meaning of these flags; depending on the flags, an existing database is opened, or a new one created.
trans-unit.target: 通过调用MsiOpenDatabase返回一个新的数据库对象。path是MSI文件的文件名；持久可以是常量 MSIDBOPEN_CREATEDIRECT ， MSIDBOPEN_CREATE ， MSIDBOPEN_DIRECT ， MSIDBOPEN_READONLY 或 MSIDBOPEN_TRANSACT 之一，并且可以包含标志 MSIDBOPEN_PATCHFILE 。有关这些标志的含义，请参见Microsoft文档。根据这些标志，将打开一个现有数据库，或者创建一个新数据库。

trans-unit.source: Return a new dictionary initialized from an optional positional argument and a possibly empty set of keyword arguments.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个由可选的位置参数和可能为空的关键字参数集初始化的新字典。

trans-unit.source: Return a possibly-empty list of path names that match pathname, which must be a string containing a path specification. pathname can be either absolute (like /usr/src/Python-1.5/Makefile) or relative (like ../../Tools/*/*.gif), and can contain shell-style wildcards. trans-unit.source: Return a proxy object that delegates method calls to a parent or sibling class of type. This is useful for accessing inherited methods that have been overridden in a class.
trans-unit.target: 返回将方法调用委托给type的父级或同级类的代理对象。这对于访问已在类中重写的继承方法很有用。

trans-unit.source: Return a proxy to object which uses a weak reference. This supports use of the proxy in most contexts instead of requiring the explicit dereferencing used with weak reference objects. The returned object will have a type of either ProxyType or CallableProxyType, depending on whether object is callable. Proxy objects are not hashable regardless of the referent; this avoids a number of problems related to their fundamentally mutable nature, and prevent their use as dictionary keys. callback is the same as the parameter of the same name to the ref() function.
trans-unit.target: 将代理返回给使用弱引用的对象。这支持在大多数情况下使用代理，而不是要求对弱引用对象使用显式取消引用。返回的对象将具有 ProxyType 或 CallableProxyType 的类型，具体取决于对象是否可调用。代理对象是不可哈希的，无论引用对象是什么。这就避免了许多与其本质上可变的性质有关的问题，并避免了将它们用作字典键。callback与 ref() 函数具有相同名称的参数相同。

trans-unit.source: Return a proxy to object which uses a weak reference. Proxy objects are not hashable regardless of the referent; this avoids a number of problems related to their fundamentally mutable nature, and prevent their use as dictionary keys. callback is the same as the parameter of the same name to the ref() function.
trans-unit.target: 将代理返回给使用弱引用的对象。这支持在大多数情况下使用代理，而不是要求对弱引用对象使用显式取消引用。返回的对象将具有 ProxyType 或 CallableProxyType 的类型，具体取决于对象是否可调用。代理对象是不可散列的，无论引用对象是什么。这就避免了许多与它们的根本可变性质有关的问题，并避免了将它们用作字典键。callback与 ref() 函数具有相同名称的参数相同。

trans-unit.source: Return a random URL-safe text string, containing nbytes random bytes. The text is Base64 encoded, so on average each byte results in approximately 1.3 characters. If nbytes is None or not supplied, a reasonable default is used.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个随机的URL安全文本字符串，其中包含nbytes个随机字节。文本是使用Base64编码的，因此平均每个字节大约可使用1.3个字符。如果nbytes为 None 或未提供，则使用合理的默认值。

trans-unit.source: Return a reader object which will iterate over lines in the given csvfile. csvfile can be any object which supports the iterator protocol and returns a string each time its __next__() method is called — file objects and list objects are both suitable. If csvfile is a file object, it should be opened with newline=''. 1 An optional dialect parameter can be given which is used to define a set of parameters specific to a particular CSV dialect. It may be an instance of a subclass of the Dialect class or one of the strings returned by the list_dialects() function. The other optional fmtparams keyword arguments can be given to override individual formatting parameters in the current dialect. For full details about the dialect and formatting parameters, see section Dialects and Formatting Parameters.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个读者对象，该对象将遍历给定csvfile中的行。csvfile可以是任何支持迭代器协议并在每次调用 __next__() 方法时都返回字符串的对象 - 文件对象和列表对象均适用。如果csvfile是文件对象，则应使用 newline='' 打开它。1可以提供可选的方言参数，该参数用于定义特定于特定CSV方言的一组参数。它可能是 Dialect 类的子类的实例，也可能是 list_dialects() 返回的字符串之一。功能。可以使用其他可选的fmtparams关键字参数来覆盖当前方言中的各个格式设置参数。有关方言和格式设置参数的完整详细信息，请参见“ 方言和格式设置参数”部分。

trans-unit.source: Return a reader object which will iterate over lines in the given csvfile. csvfile can be any object which supports the iterator protocol and returns a string each time its __next__() method is called — file objects and list objects are both suitable. The edit cursor of the textbox is initially located at the upper left hand corner of the containing window, with coordinates (0, 0). The instance’s stripspaces flag is initially on.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个文本框小部件对象。该赢的说法应该是一个诅咒窗口对象，其中的文本框将被遏制。文本框的编辑光标最初位于包含窗口的左上角，坐标为 (0, 0) 。实例的 stripspaces 标志最初处于打开状态。

trans-unit.source: Return a titlecased version of the binary sequence where words start with an uppercase ASCII character and the remaining characters are lowercase. Uncased byte values are left unmodified.
trans-unit.target: 返回二进制序列的titlecased版本,其中单词以大写ASCII字符开始,其余字符为小写。未覆盖的字节值不做修改。

trans-unit.source: Return a titlecased version of the string where words start with an uppercase character and the remaining characters are lowercase.
trans-unit.target: 返回字符串的titlecased版本,其中单词以大写字符开始,其余字符为小写。

trans-unit.source: Return a token. If tokens have been stacked using push_token(), pop a token off the stack. Otherwise, read one from the input stream. If reading encounters an immediate end-of-file, eof is returned (the empty string ('') in non-POSIX mode, and None in POSIX mode).
trans-unit.target: 返回令牌。如果令牌已使用 push_token() 进行堆叠，请从堆叠中弹出令牌。否则，请从输入流中读取一个。如果读取遇到立即结束文件， eof 被返回（空字符串（ '' 非POSIX模式），以及 None 在POSIX模式）。

trans-unit.source: Return a triple (hostname, aliaslist, ipaddrlist) where hostname is the primary host name responding to the given ip_address, aliaslist is a (possibly empty) list of alternative host names for the same address, and ipaddrlist is a list of IPv4/v6 addresses for the same interface on the same host (most likely containing only a single address). To find the fully qualified domain name, use the function getfqdn(). gethostbyaddr() supports both IPv4 and IPv6.
trans-unit.target: 返回三元组 (hostname, aliaslist, ipaddrlist) ，其中主机名是响应给定ip_address的主要主机名，aliaslist是相同地址的替代主机名的列表（可能为空），而ipaddrlist是IPv4 / v6地址的列表用于同一主机上的同一接口（很可能仅包含一个地址）。要查找完全合格的域名，请使用函数 getfqdn() 。 gethostbyaddr() 支持IPv4和IPv6。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple (rgid, egid, sgid) denoting the current process’s real, effective, and saved group ids.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个元组（rgid，egid，sgid），表示当前进程的真实，有效和已保存的组ID。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple (ruid, euid, suid) denoting the current process’s real, effective, and saved user ids.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个元组（ruid，euid，suid），表示当前进程的真实，有效和已保存的用户ID。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple (address, length) giving the current memory address and the length in elements of the buffer used to hold array’s contents. The size of the memory buffer in bytes can be computed as array.buffer_info()[1] * array.itemsize. This is occasionally useful when working with low-level (and inherently unsafe) I/O interfaces that require memory addresses, such as certain ioctl() operations. The returned numbers are valid as long as the array exists and no length-changing operations are applied to it.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个元组 (address, length) ，该元组给出当前内存地址以及用于保存数组内容的缓冲区元素的长度。内存缓冲区的大小（以字节为单位）可以计算为 array.buffer_info()[1] * array.itemsize 。在使用需要内存地址的低级（本质上不安全）的I / O接口（例如某些 ioctl() 操作）时，这有时会很有用。只要数组存在并且没有对其应用任何长度更改操作，返回的数字都是有效的。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple (fg, bg) containing the colors for the requested color pair. The value of pair_number must be between 1 and COLOR_PAIRS - 1.
trans-unit.target: 返回包含所请求颜色对的颜色的元组 (fg, bg) 。pair_number的值必须介于 1 到 COLOR_PAIRS - 1 。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple (real_value, coded_value) from a string representation. real_value can be any type. This method does no decoding in BaseCookie — it exists so it can be overridden.
trans-unit.target: 从字符串表示形式返回一个元组 (real_value, coded_value) 。 real_value 可以是任何类型。此方法在 BaseCookie 中不进行解码-它存在，因此可以重写。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple (real_value, coded_value). val can be any type, but coded_value will always be converted to a string. This method does no encoding in BaseCookie — it exists so it can be overridden.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个元组 (real_value, coded_value) 。val可以是任何类型，但是 coded_value 将始终转换为字符串。此方法在 BaseCookie 中不进行编码-它存在，因此可以重写。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple (stdout_data, stderr_data).
trans-unit.target: 返回一个元组 (stdout_data, stderr_data) 。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple (y, x) of co-ordinates of upper-left corner.
trans-unit.target: 返回左上角坐标的元组 (y, x) 。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple (y, x) of current cursor position relative to the window’s upper-left corner.
trans-unit.target: 返回相对于窗口左上角的当前光标位置的元组 (y, x) 。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple (y, x) of the height and width of the window.
trans-unit.target: 返回窗口的高度和宽度的元组 (y, x) 。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple consisting of the minimum and maximum values of all samples in the sound fragment.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个由声音片段中所有样本的最小值和最大值组成的元组。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple containing event and the current node as xml.dom.minidom.Document if event equals START_DOCUMENT, xml.dom.minidom.Element if event equals START_ELEMENT or END_ELEMENT or xml.dom.minidom.Text if event equals CHARACTERS. The current node does not contain information about its children, unless expandNode() is called.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个包含元组事件和当前节点作为 xml.dom.minidom.Document 如果事件等于 START_DOCUMENT ， xml.dom.minidom.Element 如果事件等于 START_ELEMENT 或 END_ELEMENT 或 xml.dom.minidom.Text 如果事件等于 CHARACTERS 。当前节点不包含有关其子节点的信息，除非 expandNode() 。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple containing all path names currently supported in sysconfig.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个元组，其中包含 sysconfig 当前支持的所有路径名。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple containing all schemes currently supported in sysconfig.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个包含 sysconfig 当前支持的所有方案的元组。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple containing all the subgroups of the match, from 1 up to however many groups are in the pattern. The default argument is used for groups that did not participate in the match; it defaults to None.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个包含匹配项所有子组的元组，从1到模式中的许多组。该默认参数用于那些没有参加比赛组; 它默认为 None 。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple containing names of free variables in this function.
trans-unit.target: 返回包含本函数中自由变量名称的元组。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple containing names of globals in this function.
trans-unit.target: 返回包含本函数中 globals 名称的元组。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple containing names of locals in this function.
trans-unit.target: 返回本函数中包含locals名称的元组。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple containing names of nonlocals in this function.
trans-unit.target: 返回本函数中包含非locals名称的元组。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple containing names of parameters to this function.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个包含本函数参数名称的元组。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple containing the names of methods declared in the class.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个包含类中声明的方法名称的元组。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple of class cls’s base classes, including cls, in method resolution order. No class appears more than once in this tuple. Note that the method resolution order depends on cls’s type. Unless a very peculiar user-defined metatype is in use, cls will be the first element of the tuple.
trans-unit.target: 以方法解析顺序返回类cls的基类（包括cls）的元组。在该元组中，没有一个班级出现多次。请注意，方法的解析顺序取决于cls的类型。除非使用非常特殊的用户定义的元类型，否则cls将是元组的第一个元素。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple of three items: the index in the list of the first regular expression that matches; the match object returned; and the bytes read up till and including the match.
trans-unit.target: 返回由三个项目组成的元组:第一个匹配的正则表达式在列表中的索引;返回的匹配对象;读取的字节数,直到并包括匹配。

trans-unit.source: Return a tuple of two integers, whose ratio is equal to the Fraction and with a positive denominator.
trans-unit.target: 返回两个整数的元组,其比值等于Fraction,分母为正。

trans-unit.source: Return a value equal to the first operand after rounding and having the exponent of the second operand.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个与第一个操作数四舍五入后相等的值,并具有第二个操作数的指数。

trans-unit.source: Return a value for the context variable for the current context.
trans-unit.target: 返回当前上下文的上下文变量的值。

trans-unit.source: Return a view object, by calling MSIDatabaseOpenView(). sql is the SQL statement to execute.
trans-unit.target: 通过调用 MSIDatabaseOpenView() 返回视图对象。sql是要执行的SQL语句。

trans-unit.source: Return a watcher object implementing the AbstractChildWatcher interface.
trans-unit.target: 返回实现 AbstractChildWatcher 接口的观察者对象。

trans-unit.source: Return a weak reference to object. The original object can be retrieved by calling the reference object if the referent is still alive; if the referent is no longer alive, calling the reference object will cause None to be returned. If callback is provided and not None, and the returned weakref object is still alive, the callback will be called when the object is about to be finalized; the weak reference object will be passed as the only parameter to the callback; the referent will no longer be available.
trans-unit.target: 返回对object的弱引用。如果引用对象还活着，则可以通过调用引用对象来检索原始对象。如果引用对象不再存在，则调用引用对象将导致返回 None 。如果提供了callback而不是 None ，并且返回的weakref对象仍处于活动状态，则将在该对象即将完成时调用该回调；弱引用对象将作为唯一参数传递给回调；该参考对象将不再可用。

trans-unit.source: Return a writer object responsible for converting the user’s data into delimited strings on the given file-like object. csvfile can be any object with a write() method. If csvfile is a file object, it should be opened with newline=''1. An optional dialect parameter can be given which is used to define a set of parameters specific to a particular CSV dialect. It may be an instance of a subclass of the Dialect class or one of the strings returned by the list_dialects() function. The other optional fmtparams keyword arguments can be given to override individual formatting parameters in the current dialect. For full details about the dialect and formatting parameters, see section Dialects and Formatting Parameters. To make it as easy as possible to interface with modules which implement the DB API, the value None is written as the empty string. While this isn’t a reversible transformation, it makes it easier to dump SQL NULL data values to CSV files without preprocessing the data returned from a cursor.fetch* call. All other non-string data are stringified with str() before being written.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个writer对象，该对象负责将用户数据转换为给定文件状对象上的定界字符串。csvfile可以是具有 write() 方法的任何对象。如果csvfile是文件对象，则应使用 newline='' 1打开它。可以提供可选的方言参数，该参数用于定义特定于特定CSV方言的一组参数。它可以是 Dialect 类的子类的实例，也可以是 list_dialects() 函数返回的字符串之一。其他可选的fmtparams可以提供关键字参数来覆盖当前方言中的各个格式设置参数。有关方言和格式设置参数的完整详细信息，请参见“ 方言和格式设置参数”部分。为了尽可能容易地与实现DB API的模块接口，将值 None 写为空字符串。尽管这不是可逆的转换，但它可以更轻松地将SQL NULL数据值转储到CSV文件中，而无需预处理 cursor.fetch* 调用返回的数据。所有其他非字符串数据在写入前都用 str() 进行了字符串化。

trans-unit.source: Return a year’s calendar as a complete HTML page. width (defaulting to 3) specifies the number of months per row. css is the name for the cascading style sheet to be used. None can be passed if no style sheet should be used. encoding specifies the encoding to be used for the output (defaulting to the system default encoding).
trans-unit.target: 返回一年的日历作为完整的HTML页面。width（默认为3）指定每行的月数。css是要使用的层叠样式表的名称。 None 是否应使用无样式表可以传递。encoding指定用于输出的编码（默认为系统默认编码）。

trans-unit.source: Return a year’s calendar as an HTML table. width (defaulting to 3) specifies the number of months per row.
trans-unit.target: 返回一年的日历作为HTML表格。width（默认为3）指定每行的月数。

trans-unit.source: Return all breakpoints for lineno in filename, or an empty list if none are set.
trans-unit.target: 在filename中返回lineno的所有断点，如果未设置则返回一个空列表。

trans-unit.source: Return all breakpoints in filename, or an empty list if none are set.
trans-unit.target: 返回filename中的所有断点，如果未设置，则返回一个空列表。

trans-unit.source: Return all breakpoints that are set.
trans-unit.target: 返回所有设置的断点。

trans-unit.source: Return all non-overlapping matches of pattern in string, as a list of strings. The string is scanned left-to-right, and matches are returned in the order found. If one or more groups are present in the pattern, return a list of groups; this will be a list of tuples if the pattern has more than one group. Empty matches are included in the result.
trans-unit.target: 返回所有非重叠的匹配模式的字符串，如字符串列表。该字符串被扫描的左到右，而比赛的顺序返回找到。如果模式中存在一个或多个组，则返回一个组列表；否则，返回一个列表。如果模式包含多个组，则这将是一个元组列表。空匹配项包含在结果中。

trans-unit.source: Return all tasks for an event loop.
trans-unit.target: 返回事件循环的所有任务。

trans-unit.source: Return all the members of an object in a list of (name, value) pairs sorted by name. If the optional predicate argument—which will be called with the value object of each member—is supplied, only members for which the predicate returns a true value are included.
trans-unit.target: 返回按名称排序的 (name, value) 对列表中的对象的所有成员。如果提供了可选的谓词参数（将与每个成员的 value 对象一起调用），则仅包含谓词为其返回真值的成员。

trans-unit.source: Return amount of space the text would occupy on the specified display when formatted in the current font. If no display is specified then the main application window is assumed.
trans-unit.target: 返回以当前字体格式化后,文本在指定显示器上所占的空间。如果没有指定显示器,则假定为主应用程序窗口。

trans-unit.source: Return an IPv4Address or IPv6Address object depending on the IP address passed as argument. Either IPv4 or IPv6 addresses may be supplied; integers less than 2**32 will be considered to be IPv4 by default. A ValueError is raised if address does not represent a valid IPv4 or IPv6 address.
trans-unit.target: 根据作为参数传递的IP地址返回一个 IPv4Address 或 IPv6Address 对象。可以提供IPv4或IPv6地址。小于2 ** 32的整数默认情况下将被视为IPv4。一个 ValueError 异常，如果被提升的地址并不代表一个有效的IPv4或IPv6地址。

trans-unit.source: Return an IPv4Interface or IPv6Interface object depending on the IP address passed as argument. address is a string or integer representing the IP address. Either IPv4 or IPv6 addresses may be supplied; integers less than 2**32 will be considered to be IPv4 by default. A ValueError is raised if address does not represent a valid IPv4 or IPv6 address.
trans-unit.target: 根据作为参数传递的IP地址返回 IPv4Interface 或 IPv6Interface 对象。address是代表IP地址的字符串或整数。可以提供IPv4或IPv6地址。小于2 ** 32的整数默认情况下将被视为IPv4。一个 ValueError 异常，如果被提升的地址并不代表一个有效的IPv4或IPv6地址。

trans-unit.source: Return an IPv4Network or IPv6Network object depending on the IP address passed as argument. address is a string or integer representing the IP network. Either IPv4 or IPv6 networks may be supplied; integers less than 2**32 will be considered to be IPv4 by default. strict is passed to IPv4Network or IPv6Network constructor. A ValueError is raised if address does not represent a valid IPv4 or IPv6 address, or if the network has host bits set.
trans-unit.target: 根据作为参数传递的IP地址返回一个 IPv4Network 或 IPv6Network 对象。address是代表IP网络的字符串或整数。可以提供IPv4或IPv6网络。小于2 ** 32的整数默认情况下将被视为IPv4。strict传递给 IPv4Network 或 IPv6Network 构造函数。一个 ValueError 异常，如果被提升的地址并不代表一个有效的IPv4或IPv6地址，或者如果网络中有主机位设置。

trans-unit.source: Return an MH instance representing the folder whose name is folder. A NoSuchMailboxError exception is raised if the folder does not exist.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个 MH 实例，该实例代表名称为folder的文件夹。一个 NoSuchMailboxError 如果文件夹不存在异常。

trans-unit.source: Return an Message instance whose headers are the message’s visible headers and whose body is empty.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个 Message 实例，其标题是消息的可见标题，并且其主体为空。

trans-unit.source: Return an OpenerDirector instance, which chains the handlers in the order given. handlers can be either instances of BaseHandler, or subclasses of BaseHandler (in which case it must be possible to call the constructor without any parameters). Instances of the following classes will be in front of the handlers, unless the handlers contain them, instances of them or subclasses of them: ProxyHandler (if proxy settings are detected), UnknownHandler, HTTPHandler, HTTPDefaultErrorHandler, HTTPRedirectHandler, FTPHandler, FileHandler, HTTPErrorProcessor.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个 OpenerDirector 实例，该实例按照给定的顺序链接处理程序。处理程序可以均是任实例 BaseHandler ，或子类 BaseHandler （在这种情况下，它必须能够调用构造没有任何参数）。以下类的实例将位于处理程序的前面，除非处理程序包含它们，它们的实例或它们的子类： ProxyHandler （如果检测到代理设置）， UnknownHandler ， HTTPHandler ， HTTPDefaultErrorHandler ， HTTPRedirectHandler ， FTPHandler ， FileHandler ， HTTPErrorProcessor 。

trans-unit.source: Return an iterator object. The first argument is interpreted very differently depending on the presence of the second argument. Without a second argument, object must be a collection object which supports the iteration protocol (the __iter__() method), or it must support the sequence protocol (the __getitem__() method with integer arguments starting at 0). If it does not support either of those protocols, TypeError is raised. If the second argument, sentinel, is given, then object must be a callable object. The iterator created in this case will call object with no arguments for each call to its __next__() method; if the value returned is equal to sentinel, StopIteration will be raised, otherwise the value will be returned.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个迭代器对象。根据第二个参数的存在，第一个参数的解释非常不同。如果没有第二个参数，则对象必须是支持迭代协议的集合对象（ __iter__() 方法），或者必须支持序列协议（具有从 0 开始的整数参数的 __getitem__() 方法）。如果它不支持这些协议中的任何一个，则会引发 TypeError 。如果给定第二个参数sentinel，则object必须是可调用对象。在这种情况下创建的迭代器将对其对象的每次调用都调用不带参数的对象 __next__() 方法；如果返回的值等于 sentinel，则将引发 StopIteration ，否则将返回该值。

trans-unit.source: Return an iterator which yields the same values as glob() without actually storing them all simultaneously.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个迭代器，该迭代器产生的值与 glob() 相同，而实际上并没有同时存储它们。

trans-unit.source: Return an iterator yielding match objects over all non-overlapping matches for the RE pattern in string. The string is scanned left-to-right, and matches are returned in the order found. Empty matches are included in the result.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个迭代器，该迭代器在string 模式中的RE 模式的所有非重叠匹配中产生匹配对象。该字符串被扫描的左到右，而比赛的顺序返回找到。空匹配项包含在结果中。

trans-unit.source: Return an iterator object. The first argument is interpreted very differently depending on the presence of the second argument. Without a second argument, object must be a collection object which supports the iteration protocol (the __iter__() method), or it must support the sequence protocol (the __getitem__() method with integer arguments starting at 0). If it does not support either of those protocols, TypeError is raised. If the second argument, sentinel, is given, then object must be a callable object. The iterator created in this case will call object with no arguments for each call to its __next__() method; if the value returned is equal to sentinel, StopIteration will be raised, otherwise the value will be returned.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个迭代器对象。根据第二个参数的存在，第一个参数的解释非常不同。如果没有第二个参数，则对象必须是支持迭代协议（ __iter__() 方法）的集合对象，或者它必须支持序列协议（整数参数从 0 开始的 __getitem__() 方法）。如果它不支持这些协议中的任何一个，则会引发 TypeError 。如果给定第二个参数sentinel，则object必须是可调用的对象。在这种情况下创建的迭代器将对其对象的每次调用都调用不带参数的对象 __next__() 方法；如果返回的值等于sentinel，则将引发 StopIteration ，否则将返回该值。

trans-unit.source: Return an iterator which yields the same values as glob() without actually storing them all simultaneously.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个迭代器，该迭代器产生的值与 glob() 相同，而实际上并没有同时存储它们。

trans-unit.source: Return an iterator yielding match objects over all non-overlapping matches for the RE pattern in string. The string is scanned left-to-right, and matches are returned in the order found. Empty matches are included in the result.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个迭代器，该迭代器在string类型的RE模式的所有非重叠匹配中产生匹配对象。该字符串被扫描的左到右，而比赛的顺序返回找到。空匹配项包含在结果中。

trans-unit.source: Return an absolute pathname of a file that did not exist at the time the call is made. The prefix, suffix, and dir arguments are similar to those of mkstemp(), except that bytes file names, suffix=None and prefix=None are not supported.
trans-unit.target: 返回调用时不存在的文件的绝对路径名。该前缀，后缀和DIR参数类似于那些 mkstemp() ，但字节的文件名， suffix=None 和 prefix=None ，不支持。

trans-unit.source: Return an accurate floating point sum of values in the iterable. Avoids loss of precision by tracking multiple intermediate partial sums:
trans-unit.target: 返回迭代中的精确浮点和。通过跟踪多个中间部分和,避免了精度损失。

trans-unit.source: Return an arbitrary (key, message) pair, where key is a key and message is a message representation, and delete the corresponding message. If the mailbox is empty, raise a KeyError exception. The message is represented as an instance of the appropriate format-specific Message subclass unless a custom message factory was specified when the Mailbox instance was initialized.

trans-unit.source: Return list of 5-tuples describing how to turn a into b. Each tuple is of the form (tag, i1, i2, j1, j2). The first tuple has i1 == j1 == 0, and remaining tuples have i1 equal to the i2 from the preceding tuple, and, likewise, j1 equal to the previous j2.
trans-unit.target: 返回5元组的列表，描述如何将a变成b。每个元组具有 (tag, i1, i2, j1, j2) 。第一个元组的 i1 == j1 == 0 ，其余的元组的i1等于前一个元组的i2，同样，j1等于前一个元组j2。

trans-unit.target: 返回当前进程的所有活的子进程的列表。

trans-unit.target: 返回用户所属的组ID的列表。如果组不在列表中，则将其包括在内。通常，将group指定为user的密码记录中的group ID字段。

trans-unit.source: Return list of supplemental group ids associated with the current process.

trans-unit.source: Return list of triples describing non-overlapping matching subsequences. Each triple is of the form (i, j, n), and means that a[i:i+n] == b[j:j+n]. The triples are monotonically increasing in i and j.
trans-unit.target: 返回描述非重叠匹配子序列的三元组列表。每个三元组的形式为 (i, j, n) ，表示 a[i:i+n] == b[j:j+n] 。i和j中的三元组单调增加。

trans-unit.source: Return local time as an aware datetime object. If called without arguments, return current time. Otherwise dt argument should be a datetime instance, and it is converted to the local time zone according to the system time zone database. If dt is naive (that is, dt.tzinfo is None), it is assumed to be in local time. In this case, a positive or zero value for isdst causes localtime to presume initially that summer time (for example, Daylight Saving Time) is or is not (respectively) in effect for the specified time. A negative value for isdst causes the localtime to attempt to divine whether summer time is in effect for the specified time.
trans-unit.target: 返回本地时间作为已知的日期时间对象。如果不带参数调用，则返回当前时间。否则，dt参数应为 datetime 实例，并根据系统时区数据库将其转换为本地时区。如果dt天真（即 dt.tzinfo 为 None ），则假定它是本地时间。在这种情况下，正的或零值isdst原因 localtime 最初假定夏季时间（例如，夏令时）是或不是（分别）在指定的时间的效果。为负值isdst使 localtime 尝试判断夏令时是否在指定时间内有效。

trans-unit.target: 返回消息摘要（唯一ID）列表。如果该被指定时，结果包含在形式消息的唯一ID 'response mesgnum uid ，否则结果为列表 (response, ['mesgnum uid', ...], octets) 。
